article.description: Rutgers defeated Michigan 65-50 Wednesday night to advance to Sunday's Preseason WNIT finals.
article.headline: Knights' balanced scoring ousts Michigan
article.linkText: Rutgers advances to Preseason WNIT final
article.story:
PISCATAWAY, N.J. (AP) -- Cappie Pondexter had 16 points to lead
five Rutgers players in double figures and the 15th-ranked Scarlet
Knights beat Michigan 65-50 Wednesday night in the semifinals of
the women's Preseason NIT.

Dawn McCullouch scored 14 points, Michelle Campbell had 11 and
Nikki Jett and Rebecca Richman each added 10 for the Scarlet
Knights (3-0), who advanced to Sunday's championship game against
the winner of Thursday's semifinal between UC-Santa Barbara and
Texas Tech.

Rutgers scored nine straight points to take a 9-3 lead and never
trailed again. The Scarlet Knights added runs of 5-0 and 7-0 over
the first 12 minutes of the half to build a 21-7 lead as first
Campbell (six points) and then Richman (five) dominated on the
offensive boards for second-chance points.

The Scarlet Knights led 30-22 at halftime.

Michigan got within 36-31 with 14:50 to play, but Pondexter, a
junior guard, hit two short jumpers and McCullouch added another to
build the lead back to 11.

The Scarlet Knights turned up the defensive pressure and took
their biggest lead at 65-48 with 26 seconds to play.

Rutgers held a 35-31 edge on the boards, with Richman pulling
down a team-high 12.

Jennifer Smith scored 14 of her team-high 16 points in the
second half for Michigan, which was held to 8-of-28 shooting (28
percent) in the second half.
